<h3><span style="color: #399cf8;">Case Study: Sorrento Beach Hotel</span></h3>
<em>‚ÄúThis mobile site is fantastic. We have seen many enquiries come through for our various facilities and services. Displaying other offerings like make a direct booking, contact us directly and also having the social media links front and centre has increased traffic and voice. With over 4000 Total Visits in just 3 months, we are very happy with the result. The mobile site makes us money because it drives customers to us. Literally as well as figuratively as people find us so much easier with the maps and call us here button features.‚Äù</em>

<em>Andrew Slomp, owner of Sorrento Beach Hotel</em>
<h4>About Sorrento Beach Hotel</h4>
Located just 20 minutes north of Perth City. The Sorrento Beach Hotel is one of the busiest resorts on the coast, within walking distance to Scarborough Beach, the ferry to Rottnest Island, shopping, restaurants and fishing charters. The resort itself has many functionalities and offerings.
<h4>The Challenge</h4>
Allowing holiday goers to use the maps feature, connect easily and quickly while keeping ahead of the competition.
<h4>The goMobi Solution</h4>
Optimizing the mobile site with key features and links to the website. Allowing users to quickly get directions, call and see the key offerings, images and services instantly.
<h4>Results</h4>
Quality resort Sorrento Beach Perth is in the Top 20 of most visited mobile sites. Continuing to grow from strength to strength increasing every feature consistently. Having over 4000, yes, 4000 visits in less than 3 months, the mobile site speaks for itself.

